ve sleep apnea (OSA)\n- Questionable Crohn\\'s disease\n- Depression\n\n### Discharge Medications\n1. Meropenem 1000 mg IV Q8H\n2. Ursodiol 300 mg PO TID\n3. Rifaximin 550 mg PO BID\n4. Lactulose 15 mL PO BID PRN\n5. Omeprazole 40 mg PO DAILY\n6. Levothyroxine Sodium 75 mcg PO DAILY\n7. Escitalopram Oxalate 20 mg PO DAILY\n8. Cholestyramine 4 gm PO DAILY\n9. Furosemide 40 mg PO BID\n10. Spironolactone 100 mg PO BID\n11. Ondansetron 4 mg PO BID PRN\n12. HydrOXYzine 50 mg PO QHS PRN\n13. Temazepam 15 mg PO QHS PRN\n14. Multivitamins 1 TAB PO DAILY\n\n### Physical Examination\n- **Vital Signs:** Temperature 98.7\u00b0F, Heart Rate 60-61 bpm, Blood Pressure 94-95/46-60 mmHg, Respiratory Rate 16, SpO2 95% on room air.\n- **General:** Pleasant, non-toxic appearing, sleeping comfortably in no acute distress.\n- **Neck:** Supple.\n- **Cardiovascular:** Regular rate and rhythm, S1 and S2 present, systolic murmur at the left second intercostal space.\n- **Lungs:** Clear to auscultation bilaterally; no wheezes, rales, or rhonchi.\n- **Abdomen:** Soft, tender to palpation in the right upper quadrant; Murphy\\'s sign noted as positive at discharge.\n- **Extremities:** No lower extremity edema; left-sided PICC line in place.\n- **Neurological:** Alert and oriented x3, moving all extremities bilaterally, no asterixis.",
