nal pain and nausea. Laboratory trends at discharge showed marked improvement in cholestatic markers, with Alkaline Phosphatase decreasing to 245 U/L and Total Bilirubin normalizing to 0.8 mg/dL. The patient was discharged in stable condition to complete a 7-day post-procedural course of IV Meropenem via a PICC line, with scheduled outpatient lab monitoring and hepatology follow-up for transplant listing and further endoscopic surveillance.",
